.TH "LIGHTNING-CHANNEL-MAX-HTLC-SET" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-channel-max-htlc-set \- set the maximum HTLC value for a channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning channel-max-htlc-set
.I channel_id
.I max_msat
.SH DESCRIPTION
Updates the
.B htlcmax
policy on
.I channel_id
via
.B lightning-cli setchannel
to limit the maximum single-HTLC value.
Returns an error object if the daemon is unreachable.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"ok":true}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-channel-set-fee (1),
.BR lightning-node-fee-policy (1)
